A Xero MCP (Model Context Protocol) server is an open-source bridge that enables AI agents, such as Claude, to interact with Xero accounting data through standardized protocol commands [1][2]. By integrating with the Xero API, it allows LLMs to perform tasks like creating invoices, managing contacts, and analyzing transaction data [2][3].

Several implementations exist, including the official repository [1][4] and community-driven versions like those by d4m14ndx [5] or danielreddd [6], which offer expanded toolsets. Most servers support authentication via Xero OAuth2 or bearer tokens [1][5][6].

To use the official server in a configuration file like Claude Desktop, you typically provide the command and environment credentials:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "xero": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@xeroapi/xero-mcp-server"],
      "env": {
        "XERO_CLIENT_ID": "your_client_id",
        "XERO_CLIENT_SECRET": "your_client_secret"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Reference: [1][7][6]
